                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d175</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">175</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-12-10T13:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-12-10T13:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-10T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/12–1048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Krentz</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-10T13:00:00-05:00">December 10, 1948—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68. For your info[rmation] Chi[nese] Ministry Nat[ional] Defense has requested
                    ships carrying munitions purchased from China <pb facs="0238" n="228" xml:id="pg_228"/> Aid Act $125 million grants unload at Keelung consignment
                    that portion previously destined Shanghai and Chi Combined Service Forces has
                    been instructed have personnel in Taiwan receive such supplies. First ship
                    affected by this arrangement carrying ammo, 60 percent of which to be unloaded
                    Keelung, expected arrive shortly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
